1
00:01:57,010 --> 00:01:59,140
You just never learn, do you?!

2
00:01:59,140 --> 00:02:01,810
Put me down! I'll pay later!

3
00:02:02,190 --> 00:02:02,940
With my body!

4
00:02:02,940 --> 00:02:03,650
Not you, too!

5
00:02:04,020 --> 00:02:05,610
You made some more boys cry?

6
00:02:05,610 --> 00:02:07,570
They made me mad!

7
00:02:07,570 --> 00:02:09,650
It's okay. Kids will be kids.

8
00:02:09,650 --> 00:02:11,740
They said your tangerines suck!

9
00:02:11,740 --> 00:02:12,570
They said what?!

10
00:02:12,570 --> 00:02:13,530
Bell-mère!

11
00:02:14,740 --> 00:02:16,450
Don't give in to anyone...

12
00:02:17,700 --> 00:02:21,410
Even girls need to be tough...

13
00:02:21,410 --> 00:02:23,290
It doesn't matter what people think!

14
00:02:24,370 --> 00:02:26,710
Don't resent the world
you were born into...

15
00:02:30,380 --> 00:02:34,470
And no matter what happens,
don't forget how to smile.

16
00:02:37,640 --> 00:02:43,640
– Bell-mère!
– Bell-mère!

17
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:49,570
Under my rule,
anyone who can't pay dies!

18
00:02:49,570 --> 00:02:52,280
Got that, you worms?!

19
00:02:55,450 --> 00:02:56,280
What's this?

20
00:02:57,410 --> 00:02:58,410
A sea chart?

21
00:02:58,410 --> 00:02:59,370
No!

22
00:02:59,780 --> 00:03:01,870
I drew that! It's important to me!

23
00:03:01,870 --> 00:03:03,370
Give it back!

24
00:03:03,370 --> 00:03:04,830
You drew this?

25
00:03:04,830 --> 00:03:06,970
Give it back!

26
00:03:05,460 --> 00:03:06,970
Nami! No!

27
00:03:07,540 --> 00:03:08,670
Oh?

28
00:03:09,170 --> 00:03:11,000
This ain't half bad.

29
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:14,590
We can use this brat! Grab her!

30
00:03:14,590 --> 00:03:15,720
Right!

31
00:03:15,720 --> 00:03:17,260
No!

32
00:03:17,260 --> 00:03:19,760
Lemme go! Lemme go! No!

33
00:03:20,140 --> 00:03:22,220
Let Nami go! Let go!

34
00:03:21,010 --> 00:03:22,220
Stop!

35
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:24,480
You got your money!

36
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:26,480
You swore you wouldn't hurt her!

37
00:03:26,480 --> 00:03:29,690
And I won't. I'm just
borrowing her for a bit.

38
00:03:29,690 --> 00:03:31,440
Mr. Gen, help me!

39
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:33,110
Keep your hands off them!

40
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:34,110
Kuroobi.

41
00:03:39,070 --> 00:03:39,910
Mr. Gen...!

42
00:03:40,700 --> 00:03:42,290
Mr. Gen! Mr. Gen!

43
00:03:42,830 --> 00:03:44,250
Mr. Gen!

44
00:03:50,130 --> 00:03:52,840
Don't worry... I'll save you, Nami...

45
00:03:53,380 --> 00:03:55,300
I won't let you through...

46
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:58,800
No! It's okay!
You don't need to save me!

47
00:03:59,430 --> 00:04:00,090
Please!

48
00:04:00,090 --> 00:04:00,890
Let's end this.

49
00:04:00,890 --> 00:04:02,350
I'll... save–

50
00:04:05,640 --> 00:04:09,400
I don't want anyone else to die!

51
00:04:17,950 --> 00:04:22,070
They sank every
last one of our ships...

52
00:04:22,070 --> 00:04:26,540
Our plan to have Nojiko
and Nami escape to sea...

53
00:04:26,540 --> 00:04:28,000
was far too optimistic.

54
00:04:28,750 --> 00:04:31,500
Just as I feared,
the Marines won't help us.

55
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:33,380
This is his island, now.

56
00:04:33,380 --> 00:04:35,880
Bell-mère knew exactly
what would happen!

57
00:04:36,380 --> 00:04:40,720
She knew how pirates operate
from her time in the Marines!

58
00:04:41,260 --> 00:04:44,350
And she knew nobody
was going to get away...

59
00:04:48,940 --> 00:04:51,150
They took Nami with them.

60
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:53,060
What am I...

61
00:04:53,060 --> 00:04:55,070
supposed to do now...

62
00:04:55,690 --> 00:04:57,320
Bell-mère?

63
00:04:59,860 --> 00:05:02,530
We've found out where
the Arlong Pirates are!

64
00:05:02,530 --> 00:05:05,620
It seems they intend to
settle down on this island!

65
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:07,410
It's time to decide!

66
00:05:07,790 --> 00:05:09,660
Do we fight now, defiant to the end?!

67
00:05:09,660 --> 00:05:12,920
Or do we bide our time, hoping
the government comes to rescue us,

68
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:15,550
while living under
the executioner's axe?!

69
00:05:15,550 --> 00:05:16,750
It's one or the other!

70
00:05:17,420 --> 00:05:20,470
Only Marine Headquarters
stands a chance against them.

71
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:23,970
But they have their hands
full in the Grand Line.

72
00:05:23,970 --> 00:05:28,100
The chances of them coming all
the way out here are slim to none!

73
00:05:28,100 --> 00:05:31,480
And I can't abandon Nami!

74
00:05:31,980 --> 00:05:32,810
I'll fight!

75
00:05:35,570 --> 00:05:36,940
I'll fight, too!

76
00:05:36,940 --> 00:05:40,030
I can't just go on
knowing I abandoned a child!

77
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:42,530
Everyone here is family!

78
00:05:42,530 --> 00:05:45,620
Even if I die fighting them,
I'm gonna save Nami!

79
00:05:45,620 --> 00:05:47,990
Bell-mère gave her life
to protect those kids!

80
00:05:48,410 --> 00:05:49,870
This time, we'll give 'em hell!

81
00:05:49,870 --> 00:05:52,580
If any one of us fights back,
we'll all be blamed anyway!

82
00:06:00,380 --> 00:06:01,340
Nami!

83
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:03,550
Nami!

84
00:06:03,550 --> 00:06:04,430
Hey, Nami!

85
00:06:04,430 --> 00:06:05,340
Are you alright?!

86
00:06:05,930 --> 00:06:07,510
Nami! Nami!

87
00:06:08,390 --> 00:06:11,730
Are you okay? Are you hurt?
Did they do anything to you?

88
00:06:14,520 --> 00:06:15,270
Nami?

89
00:06:15,270 --> 00:06:18,320
I'm... joining...

90
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:19,150
Huh?

91
00:06:19,940 --> 00:06:21,530
I'm joining...

92
00:06:21,530 --> 00:06:23,740
the Arlong Pirates...

93
00:06:24,610 --> 00:06:26,950
to draw sea charts
as their cartographer!

94
00:06:31,950 --> 00:06:34,040
What are you saying, Nami?

95
00:06:34,790 --> 00:06:36,540
Are you thinking straight?

96
00:06:36,540 --> 00:06:39,250
Did they do something
horrible to you?

97
00:06:39,250 --> 00:06:40,840
They did, didn't they?

98
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:41,510
No.

99
00:06:41,510 --> 00:06:42,880
They threatened you, right?!

100
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:44,300
Tell us!

101
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:43,840
No!

102
00:06:44,300 --> 00:06:46,340
Let go of me!

103
00:06:46,340 --> 00:06:47,390
Nami...!

104
00:06:47,890 --> 00:06:48,800
Nami!

105
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:55,310
Th-That tattoo... Arlong's flag...!

106
00:06:56,440 --> 00:06:57,190
You...

107
00:06:57,860 --> 00:06:58,980
Nami...

108
00:07:00,230 --> 00:07:01,860
Check it out...

109
00:07:01,860 --> 00:07:04,360
They gave me all this money...

110
00:07:07,370 --> 00:07:10,450
and they say they'll
buy me whatever I want...

111
00:07:10,450 --> 00:07:11,740
Nami!

112
00:07:13,290 --> 00:07:14,870
Unforgivable! Despicable!

113
00:07:14,870 --> 00:07:17,580
Joining those guys is
absolutely unforgivable!

114
00:07:17,580 --> 00:07:19,460
Not them! No way!

115
00:07:19,460 --> 00:07:21,800
Don't you know what
kind of people they are?!

116
00:07:22,210 --> 00:07:23,340
Who cares?!

117
00:07:23,340 --> 00:07:26,430
If following the rules
gets me killed like Bell-mère,

118
00:07:26,430 --> 00:07:29,430
then I'd rather break them!

119
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:32,970
I can't believe you...

120
00:07:33,430 --> 00:07:35,100
Bell-mère...

121
00:07:36,190 --> 00:07:39,270
Bell-mère sacrificed
her life to save us!

122
00:07:39,270 --> 00:07:40,110
How can you just–

123
00:07:40,110 --> 00:07:41,900
That's enough, Nojiko.

124
00:07:42,570 --> 00:07:43,860
Leave, Nami!

125
00:07:43,860 --> 00:07:46,700
Never show your face
in this village again!

126
00:07:54,160 --> 00:07:55,330
Nami!

127
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:01,840
How could she be so blind?

128
00:08:02,670 --> 00:08:08,090
Did she never see...
Bell-mère as her mother?!

129
00:08:18,390 --> 00:08:19,730
No, that's not true...

130
00:08:20,860 --> 00:08:23,570
Nami loved Bell-mère...

131
00:08:30,820 --> 00:08:31,870
Hey...

132
00:08:32,490 --> 00:08:34,870
Didn't Bell-mère say...

133
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:37,370
that, if we survive...

134
00:08:37,910 --> 00:08:40,750
we'd be happy someday?

135
00:08:41,330 --> 00:08:43,090
She said we'd be so happy.

136
00:08:45,250 --> 00:08:46,010
Yeah.

137
00:08:46,550 --> 00:08:48,970
After Arlong dragged me off,

138
00:08:48,970 --> 00:08:51,890
five Marine ships came
to capture him.

139
00:08:51,890 --> 00:08:54,390
He sank them like they were nothing.

140
00:08:54,930 --> 00:08:57,930
I don't think they'll
send any more help.

141
00:08:57,930 --> 00:09:01,270
So I have to take matters
into my own hands.

142
00:09:02,350 --> 00:09:04,020
I made a deal with Arlong...

143
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:06,650
to buy Cocoyashi Village.

144
00:09:06,650 --> 00:09:08,400
The whole village?

145
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:10,150
For 100 million berries.

146
00:09:12,280 --> 00:09:15,370
Once I buy it, we'll all be free.

147
00:09:15,370 --> 00:09:17,910
No one else will have to die.

148
00:09:17,910 --> 00:09:21,120
In exchange, I have to join
his crew and draw sea charts.

149
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:23,630
One hundred million berries, though?!

150
00:09:23,630 --> 00:09:25,420
How could anyone ever earn–

151
00:09:25,420 --> 00:09:27,170
I'll get that money!

152
00:09:27,170 --> 00:09:28,510
No matter what it takes!

153
00:09:28,960 --> 00:09:33,220
Since everyone's working so hard
to scrape together tribute, I'm on my own.

154
00:09:33,970 --> 00:09:37,770
If I ask anyone for help,
more people will just get hurt.

155
00:09:44,110 --> 00:09:45,610
It's not gonna be easy, y'know...

156
00:09:45,610 --> 00:09:46,400
I know.

157
00:09:47,270 --> 00:09:51,530
Staying with the people who
killed Bell-mère will hurt.

158
00:09:52,110 --> 00:09:53,530
I'll be fine.

159
00:09:53,530 --> 00:09:56,660
I'll put on a big smile,
even when I look at him!

160
00:09:56,660 --> 00:09:58,580
I've decided not to cry anymore.

161
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:03,620
From here on out,
I'll fight on my own!

162
00:10:21,350 --> 00:10:23,600
Nami was only ten.

163
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:26,690
Can you imagine how hard
of a choice it was

164
00:10:26,690 --> 00:10:28,820
to fight and survive on her own?

165
00:10:29,650 --> 00:10:33,360
For the sake of her village,
she made that deal...

166
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:34,110
She...

167
00:10:34,990 --> 00:10:38,080
I'll make those bastards
pay for hurting–

168
00:10:39,030 --> 00:10:41,000
Why... Big... Sister...?

169
00:10:41,620 --> 00:10:42,790
I told you!

170
00:10:42,790 --> 00:10:45,370
I came here to tell you to stop!

171
00:10:45,370 --> 00:10:47,750
If you keep blabbing
about being her friend,

172
00:10:47,750 --> 00:10:49,500
Arlong will get suspicious.

173
00:10:49,920 --> 00:10:52,670
Her eight years of struggling
will all be for nothing!

174
00:10:53,380 --> 00:10:55,550
She's already suffered enough.

175
00:10:56,340 --> 00:10:59,310
When you have to fight alone...

176
00:10:59,310 --> 00:11:02,810
nothing is more painful
than people calling you friend!

177
00:11:16,950 --> 00:11:19,620
Get back here! Damn brat!

178
00:11:19,620 --> 00:11:22,120
How dare you steal our treasure?!

179
00:11:22,540 --> 00:11:24,330
Stealing from pirates?!

180
00:11:24,750 --> 00:11:26,120
Yeah!

181
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:29,590
These days, the sea is crawling
with them! So I'm cashing in!

182
00:11:29,920 --> 00:11:31,880
That's what they get!

183
00:11:31,880 --> 00:11:34,220
But you're all banged up!

184
00:11:34,220 --> 00:11:38,180
Yeah, I sorta screwed up.
But check it out! One million berries!

185
00:11:38,180 --> 00:11:40,850
Who cares?! We need
to hurry and treat those cuts!

186
00:11:40,850 --> 00:11:42,770
I'm fine! It's nothing!

187
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:46,100
No one will ever find it here!

188
00:11:46,100 --> 00:11:48,810
I'll stash my money
here, little by little,

189
00:11:48,810 --> 00:11:51,320
and by the time it's full,
I'll have 100 million!

190
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:56,820
I have a long way to go...

191
00:11:58,320 --> 00:12:00,030
One hundred million berries...

192
00:12:02,660 --> 00:12:06,620
It's taken a long time...
but I'm just seven million away.

193
00:12:06,620 --> 00:12:09,830
These days, I can score
that much in one run!

194
00:12:10,540 --> 00:12:11,750
Just...

195
00:12:11,750 --> 00:12:14,800
one more trip,
and it'll finally be over...

196
00:12:15,670 --> 00:12:20,890
Everyone in Cocoyashi Village—
and I—will be free of Arlong.

197
00:12:20,890 --> 00:12:22,510
And then...

198
00:12:22,930 --> 00:12:25,020
And then, I think...

199
00:12:25,560 --> 00:12:28,730
I can finally smile from
the bottom of my heart...

200
00:12:31,650 --> 00:12:33,270
Bell-mère.

201
00:12:49,920 --> 00:12:52,920
What business do
the Marines have with Nami?

202
00:12:53,290 --> 00:12:56,630
No need to ask questions.
Simply lead the way.

203
00:12:59,300 --> 00:13:03,180
Why does that guy have
a pinwheel on his head?

204
00:13:03,850 --> 00:13:05,260
Awesome!

205
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:15,320
Guess I'll get cracking
on my final heist!

206
00:13:20,570 --> 00:13:21,700
Mr. Gen?

207
00:13:21,700 --> 00:13:23,200
And the Marines?

208
00:13:27,910 --> 00:13:30,410
Are you the thief they call Nami?

209
00:13:32,370 --> 00:13:37,340
We've received a tip that you've been
hiding treasure stolen from pirates.

210
00:13:38,340 --> 00:13:43,720
And all plundered goods
are government property.

211
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:47,810
I'll give you a warning.

212
00:13:47,810 --> 00:13:50,060
I'm an officer of the Arlong Pirates.

213
00:13:50,060 --> 00:13:53,150
Mess with me, and Arlong
won't stand by quietly!

214
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:55,900
Silly girl.

215
00:13:55,900 --> 00:13:59,650
Do you think you're dealing
with me on equal footing?

216
00:13:59,650 --> 00:14:01,200
Find the stolen goods!

217
00:14:03,200 --> 00:14:04,110
Wait!

218
00:14:09,620 --> 00:14:12,120
Don't you dare!

219
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:19,960
Is this really what the Marines
should be doing right now?!

220
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:23,840
The Arlong Pirates have murdered
innocents and destroyed entire towns!

221
00:14:23,840 --> 00:14:25,050
You know that!

222
00:14:25,550 --> 00:14:29,260
He rules this island with an iron fist,
trampling lives into the dirt!

223
00:14:29,260 --> 00:14:31,060
Is that how the government works?!

224
00:14:31,060 --> 00:14:34,600
Busting petty thieves while
turning a blind eye to all of this?!

225
00:14:36,190 --> 00:14:38,360
Watch how you speak to me.

226
00:14:38,360 --> 00:14:39,530
Continue searching!

227
00:14:39,940 --> 00:14:44,530
For years now, the people of this island
have been waiting for you to come help them!

228
00:14:44,910 --> 00:14:48,030
How can you just
ignore them all for this?!

229
00:14:48,410 --> 00:14:51,200
Captain! This tangerine
orchard seems suspicious!

230
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:52,000
Dig it up!

231
00:14:55,870 --> 00:14:59,500
Keep your filthy hands off of
Bell-mère's tangerine orchard!

232
00:15:02,460 --> 00:15:04,220
I won't let you take that money!

233
00:15:04,220 --> 00:15:06,470
That money is... That money is...

234
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:12,720
That money is the key
to Cocoyashi Village's freedom!

235
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:16,940
What gives you the right
to take it away, Marine?!

236
00:15:18,940 --> 00:15:20,320
Oh?

237
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:23,900
A backwater village sheriff,
talking back to a Marine captain?

238
00:15:24,900 --> 00:15:26,280
Mr. Gen...

239
00:15:26,280 --> 00:15:28,240
How do you know about that?

240
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:34,080
I've always known, Nami.

241
00:15:36,460 --> 00:15:39,960
Back then, I couldn't
believe how you behaved,

242
00:15:39,960 --> 00:15:41,840
so I confronted Nojiko afterward.

243
00:15:41,840 --> 00:15:44,260
Everyone in the village
has known since then

244
00:15:44,260 --> 00:15:48,800
that you stayed with
the Arlong Pirates to save the village.

245
00:15:49,180 --> 00:15:52,180
We only feigned ignorance.

246
00:15:52,180 --> 00:15:55,060
We thought our hopes
would keep you

247
00:15:55,060 --> 00:15:58,270
from running away from Arlong,
if you ever decided to.

248
00:15:58,810 --> 00:16:00,520
You can't be serious...

249
00:16:02,980 --> 00:16:05,900
Whatever are you talking about?

250
00:16:05,900 --> 00:16:10,320
You're saying all
the villagers are thieves,

251
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:11,700
and we should arrest them?

252
00:16:11,700 --> 00:16:16,290
He's saying that each and every
one of us is fighting just to survive!

253
00:16:16,710 --> 00:16:20,670
But only because we can't
rely on the government!

254
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:24,710
If you're not here to help us,
then get the hell out of here!

255
00:16:25,260 --> 00:16:28,590
Screw around and Arlong
will sink your ship, too!

256
00:16:28,590 --> 00:16:30,470
Arlong, you say?

257
00:16:30,470 --> 00:16:32,300
I wouldn't be so sure...

258
00:16:34,600 --> 00:16:36,180
You still haven't found it?!

259
00:16:36,180 --> 00:16:39,480
We're looking for 100 million
berries here! Not a grain of rice!

260
00:16:40,850 --> 00:16:42,310
Hey, you!

261
00:16:42,310 --> 00:16:43,940
How do you know
how much there is?!

262
00:16:45,780 --> 00:16:47,950
Oh, the 100 million?

263
00:16:47,950 --> 00:16:51,320
Well, let's just call it a hunch.

264
00:17:02,210 --> 00:17:03,420
Don't tell me he...

265
00:17:09,010 --> 00:17:12,010
Don't tell me Arlong sent you here?!

266
00:17:13,510 --> 00:17:15,390
Who can say?

267
00:17:15,390 --> 00:17:21,560
We're simply dealing with theft
as any civil servant would.

268
00:17:21,560 --> 00:17:23,980
You damn government thugs!

269
00:17:23,980 --> 00:17:26,940
How could the Marines
stoop to being pirate lackeys?!

270
00:17:29,240 --> 00:17:30,740
Arlong!

271
00:17:31,110 --> 00:17:32,490
I found it!

272
00:17:40,790 --> 00:17:42,750
This is incredible!

273
00:17:42,750 --> 00:17:45,960
To think a girl like you
could gather all of this!

274
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:48,260
It's all ragged and
stained with blood...

275
00:17:48,260 --> 00:17:50,420
No matter! Money is money!

276
00:17:53,550 --> 00:17:56,350
And thirty percent of it is all mine!

277
00:17:56,350 --> 00:17:58,270
Don't touch that...

278
00:17:58,770 --> 00:18:02,020
Don't touch that... Don't touch that...

279
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:04,350
Nami...!

280
00:18:04,350 --> 00:18:06,940
Don't touch that...!
Don't touch that...!

281
00:18:06,940 --> 00:18:08,570
Don't touch that!

282
00:18:24,290 --> 00:18:25,630
Nami...!

283
00:18:31,130 --> 00:18:31,760
Nojiko?!

284
00:18:32,670 --> 00:18:33,970
Nojiko!

285
00:18:39,350 --> 00:18:41,810
Doctor! Doctor!

286
00:18:42,810 --> 00:18:44,690
What is it, Mr. Gen?!

287
00:18:44,690 --> 00:18:46,100
Nojiko's been shot!

288
00:18:46,100 --> 00:18:47,310
By who?!

289
00:18:47,310 --> 00:18:48,440
The Marines!

290
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:49,270
The Marines?

291
00:18:54,610 --> 00:18:55,570
Nami...

292
00:18:56,160 --> 00:18:57,910
Hey, Nami!

293
00:18:57,910 --> 00:19:00,240
What's up? Need help with anything?

294
00:19:02,580 --> 00:19:04,000
You're still here?!

295
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:08,750
This has nothing to do with you!
Just leave the damn island already!

296
00:19:15,680 --> 00:19:17,220
Arlong!

297
00:19:17,220 --> 00:19:20,140
You really want me to free
your village that badly?

298
00:19:20,510 --> 00:19:22,180
Arlong!

299
00:19:22,180 --> 00:19:25,190
Gather up 100 million berries
and bring it to me.

300
00:19:25,190 --> 00:19:28,980
If you do that, I'll let you
and the village go.

301
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:30,730
Arlong!

302
00:19:30,730 --> 00:19:34,990
When it comes to money,
I'd rather die than break a promise.

303
00:19:34,990 --> 00:19:37,110
I don't care how long it takes.

304
00:19:37,110 --> 00:19:38,780
I'm a fishman of my word.

305
00:19:39,620 --> 00:19:41,120
Arlong!

306
00:19:45,750 --> 00:19:47,710
Man, what's her deal?

307
00:19:49,840 --> 00:19:51,380
Arlong!

308
00:19:53,420 --> 00:19:54,420
Oh?

309
00:19:54,420 --> 00:19:58,010
Why the long face,
my capable cartographer?

310
00:19:58,010 --> 00:20:00,260
What's with the scowl?

311
00:20:00,850 --> 00:20:04,770
Those Marines you've been
paying off stole all my money!

312
00:20:05,520 --> 00:20:09,770
I thought when it came to money,
you'd rather die than break a promise!

313
00:20:09,770 --> 00:20:11,270
Why?!

314
00:20:11,270 --> 00:20:13,480
And when exactly
did I break our promise?

315
00:20:13,900 --> 00:20:16,320
Don't give me that!
Those Marines of yours–

316
00:20:18,530 --> 00:20:21,160
Like I said, when
did I break our promise?

317
00:20:21,160 --> 00:20:22,200
Let's hear it!

318
00:20:30,290 --> 00:20:32,170
Damn you...

319
00:20:32,170 --> 00:20:34,250
Damn you! Damn you!

320
00:20:36,210 --> 00:20:37,340
Ah, I get it now!

321
00:20:37,340 --> 00:20:39,180
So your money's been stolen?

322
00:20:39,180 --> 00:20:41,720
That's a damn shame.

323
00:20:41,720 --> 00:20:44,060
But, hey. A deal's a deal.

324
00:20:44,060 --> 00:20:47,060
If you can't bring me 100 million berries,

325
00:20:47,060 --> 00:20:51,230
I'm afraid I can't return your village.

326
00:20:52,650 --> 00:20:53,690
You scumbag!

327
00:20:56,780 --> 00:20:58,950
Hey, it's only 100 million berries!

328
00:20:58,950 --> 00:21:01,660
Just start saving up again!

329
00:21:04,700 --> 00:21:07,500
Or maybe you're thinking
of running away?

330
00:21:08,960 --> 00:21:13,920
Just remember, if you do,
I'll kill everyone in Cocoyashi Village.

331
00:21:17,670 --> 00:21:18,920
Nami...

332
00:21:18,920 --> 00:21:21,680
We only feigned ignorance.

333
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:24,930
We thought our hopes
would keep you

334
00:21:24,930 --> 00:21:28,730
from running away from Arlong,
if you ever decided to.

335
00:21:33,650 --> 00:21:34,650
Oh?

336
00:21:34,650 --> 00:21:36,780
Running after all, huh?

337
00:21:39,860 --> 00:21:41,700
Shouldn't we chase her down?

338
00:21:41,700 --> 00:21:43,820
Chase? What for?

339
00:21:44,320 --> 00:21:46,830
She won't run away.

340
00:21:46,830 --> 00:21:51,330
She could never abandon
the lives of the villagers.

341
00:21:52,330 --> 00:21:55,210
You certainly do know
how to play dirty...

342
00:21:55,210 --> 00:21:59,420
As if I'd let a cartographer
of Nami's caliber just leave.

343
00:21:59,420 --> 00:22:02,680
But I'm not completely heartless.

344
00:22:04,180 --> 00:22:09,270
I'll let her go, alright... after she charts every sea in the world!

345
00:22:11,770 --> 00:22:15,400
That'll take decades!

346
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:18,190
You couldn't do that
in a hundred years!

347
00:22:26,910 --> 00:22:28,740
Enough is enough! Arm yourselves!

348
00:22:28,740 --> 00:22:29,830
We'll fight!

349
00:22:34,250 --> 00:22:38,750
Mr. Gen! Everyone!
Please don't do anything stupid!

350
00:22:38,750 --> 00:22:41,420
You can't die! It'll all be over!

351
00:22:42,010 --> 00:22:45,140
You have to survive,
or it was all for nothing!

352
00:22:45,140 --> 00:22:47,180
Eight years ago...

353
00:22:47,510 --> 00:22:50,680
we swore not to throw away our lives!

354
00:22:50,680 --> 00:22:53,180
No matter how
demeaning their rule was,

355
00:22:53,850 --> 00:22:58,650
we swore we'd endure it patiently
as long as Nami kept on smiling!

356
00:22:58,650 --> 00:23:01,360
But this is their answer!

357
00:23:01,740 --> 00:23:06,320
Now that our village's only chance
for freedom is gone, there's no hope left!

358
00:23:06,320 --> 00:23:07,240
Above all else,

359
00:23:07,780 --> 00:23:12,200
we have to make those fishmen pay
for toying with that girl's heart!

360
00:23:12,200 --> 00:23:13,000
Sound good?!

361
00:23:13,660 --> 00:23:15,250
Of course! Let's go!

362
00:23:15,250 --> 00:23:19,040
For the past eight years,
we've always been ready to fight!

363
00:23:19,460 --> 00:23:22,170
I'll be damned if I spend
another day under their rule!

364
00:23:24,130 --> 00:23:26,220
Wait, everyone!

365
00:23:27,760 --> 00:23:29,050
Nami!

366
00:23:32,350 --> 00:23:33,850
Just a little more!

367
00:23:33,850 --> 00:23:35,480
Just wait a little more!

368
00:23:35,480 --> 00:23:37,730
I'll work hard again!

369
00:23:37,730 --> 00:23:39,770
I'll save up the money again!

370
00:23:40,270 --> 00:23:41,900
It'll be easy this time!

371
00:23:41,900 --> 00:23:46,150
I'm used to it! It'll be okay!
There's nothing to worry about!

372
00:23:47,070 --> 00:23:49,570
This is nothing
compared to back then!

373
00:23:51,830 --> 00:23:53,790
I don't want anyone else to die!

374
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:55,410
Everyone!

375
00:23:55,410 --> 00:23:58,040
I'm fine, really! I'll be okay!

376
00:24:03,960 --> 00:24:05,590
That's enough.

377
00:24:05,590 --> 00:24:07,680
Even you must know it's over.

378
00:24:08,550 --> 00:24:13,010
You've been so brave, bearing the burden
of the entire village for all these years...

379
00:24:13,010 --> 00:24:16,390
Joining them must have hurt more

380
00:24:16,390 --> 00:24:18,980
than being stabbed through the heart.

381
00:24:19,980 --> 00:24:22,360
You've done so well.

382
00:24:23,860 --> 00:24:25,150
Mr. Gen...

383
00:24:31,280 --> 00:24:33,410
Leave the village now.

384
00:24:35,080 --> 00:24:35,830
Mr. Gen?!

385
00:24:36,870 --> 00:24:38,330
Do it, Nami.

386
00:24:38,330 --> 00:24:39,710
Wh-What?!

387
00:24:40,460 --> 00:24:41,460
Nami, sweetheart...

388
00:24:41,460 --> 00:24:42,540
Nami...

389
00:24:43,670 --> 00:24:46,920
You have a dream, and you know
how to take care of yourself.

390
00:24:46,920 --> 00:24:48,680
Nojiko! Everyone!

391
00:24:50,180 --> 00:24:51,510
I won't let you go!

392
00:24:52,680 --> 00:24:54,180
Stop it, everyone!

393
00:24:54,180 --> 00:24:57,060
I can't watch anyone else get hurt!

394
00:24:59,690 --> 00:25:00,810
They'll kill you!

395
00:25:01,810 --> 00:25:03,150
We know.

396
00:25:08,990 --> 00:25:12,320
It's no use! We've made up our minds!

397
00:25:16,040 --> 00:25:17,620
Get out of our way, Nami!

398
00:25:19,620 --> 00:25:21,170
Let's go, everyone!

399
00:25:21,170 --> 00:25:24,460
Even if we can't win,
we'll give 'em hell!

400
00:26:00,580 --> 00:26:03,000
Arlong...!

401
00:26:04,710 --> 00:26:07,340
Arlong! Arlong!

402
00:26:09,590 --> 00:26:10,340
Arlong!

403
00:26:10,340 --> 00:26:14,890
Arlong! Arlong! Arlong! Arlong!

404
00:26:14,890 --> 00:26:15,470
Ar–

405
00:26:21,100 --> 00:26:22,440
Luffy...

406
00:26:26,190 --> 00:26:27,650
What do you want?

407
00:26:27,650 --> 00:26:29,780
You don't know anything.

408
00:26:29,780 --> 00:26:33,570
You have no idea what's been
going on here for the past eight years!

409
00:26:33,570 --> 00:26:35,320
No, I don't.

410
00:26:36,120 --> 00:26:37,700
This has nothing to do with you!

411
00:26:38,540 --> 00:26:41,160
I already told you to get
off this damn island!

412
00:26:41,160 --> 00:26:43,160
Yeah, you did.

413
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:44,420
Then, leave!

414
00:26:44,420 --> 00:26:45,790
I don't need you!

415
00:26:45,790 --> 00:26:48,130
Get lost! Go! Leave!

416
00:26:48,130 --> 00:26:49,380
Go away!

417
00:26:49,380 --> 00:26:52,880
Beat it! Get the hell out of here! Go!

418
00:26:52,880 --> 00:26:54,430
Leave...!

419
00:27:07,810 --> 00:27:08,980
Luffy...

420
00:27:10,480 --> 00:27:11,860
Help me...

421
00:27:24,120 --> 00:27:26,670
Of course I will!

422
00:27:29,540 --> 00:27:31,710
Hands off my treasure!

423
00:27:33,880 --> 00:27:35,220
Luffy...

424
00:27:41,680 --> 00:27:42,390
Let's go.

425
00:27:44,180 --> 00:27:45,140
Right!

426
00:27:44,180 --> 00:27:45,140
Right!

427
00:27:44,180 --> 00:27:45,140
Right!

428
00:27:49,520 --> 00:27:50,570
Hey!

429
00:27:50,570 --> 00:27:52,360
Are you guys alright?!

430
00:27:52,360 --> 00:27:54,320
Did Arlong do this to you?!

431
00:27:55,860 --> 00:27:57,070
Move aside.

432
00:27:57,950 --> 00:28:00,580
We have business with the fishmen.

433
00:28:01,330 --> 00:28:03,830
When we found out
the truth about Big Sis Nami,

434
00:28:03,830 --> 00:28:07,830
we felt like all we could do
was try to take down Arlong.

435
00:28:07,830 --> 00:28:10,340
So we challenged him...

436
00:28:10,340 --> 00:28:12,960
...but we lost by a hair.

437
00:28:14,800 --> 00:28:19,050
Sorry, but we can't let you pass!
You guys don't stand a chance!

438
00:28:19,050 --> 00:28:20,010
What?!

439
00:28:20,350 --> 00:28:24,430
We're waiting for a certain
crew to show up, you see!

440
00:28:25,060 --> 00:28:26,520
A certain crew?

441
00:28:26,980 --> 00:28:28,600
I'd bet my life on it.

442
00:28:29,100 --> 00:28:31,610
They will come!

443
00:28:46,700 --> 00:28:47,460
– It's them!
– It's them!

444
00:29:03,470 --> 00:29:04,560
Those guys...?

445
00:29:04,560 --> 00:29:07,600
Just who are they?

446
00:29:08,060 --> 00:29:10,690
This island's only hope of survival.

447
00:29:10,690 --> 00:29:15,530
If they can't beat them, this island—
no, the entire East Blue—is finished!

448
00:29:16,230 --> 00:29:19,610
Those four men
are here to turn the tide.

449
00:29:19,610 --> 00:29:23,120
Burn their faces into your minds!

450
00:29:32,040 --> 00:29:33,170
Outta the way!

451
00:29:40,220 --> 00:29:45,050
Hey, do you think those two clowns
were part of Zoro's crew?

452
00:29:45,430 --> 00:29:48,180
Zoro's? They seemed
too weak for that.

453
00:29:48,180 --> 00:29:49,850
They're not even worth killing.

454
00:29:49,850 --> 00:29:51,640
You got that right!

455
00:30:05,200 --> 00:30:06,530
What the hell?!

456
00:30:09,250 --> 00:30:11,370
Which one of you is Arlong?!

